cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach for training generative adversarial networks (GANs) in the context of natural language tasks, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories within computer science. The focus on GANs and their optimization suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The use of natural language tasks suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. The paper's focus on optimization and the use of neural networks suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of GANs for image generation suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
